    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family containing around 1,450 species of moths; many are native to the tropics, but species are found globally. They are distinguished by being moderate to large in size, having rapid, sustained flying ability, narrow wings and streamlined abdomens.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
